      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (coarse 0.8 mm, medium 0.5 mm, fine 0.35 mm global seed with local refinement at screw-rod interface). GCI values: stiffness 0.31%, yield force 0.48%, force at 40 mm 0.62%. All below 1% threshold. Fine mesh selected for production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual norms below 1e-5 for all load steps; energy balance error < 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Newton–Raphson iterations converged to force residual norm < 1e-6 for all 11 simulation instances. Energy balance monitored via Ansys ENERGYTRACKER; maximum imbalance 0.04%. No unconverged increments recorded."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented modelling protocol; independent peer review of boundary conditions, material assignments, and loading definitions.",
      "rationale": "Modelling protocol document v2.1 followed by primary analyst. Independent review by second analyst confirmed boundary conditions (fixed base plate, displacement-controlled crosshead at 10 mm/min equivalent), material assignments (Ti-6Al-4V elastic-plastic), and contact definitions. Two discrepancies found and corrected prior to production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model validated against coupon-level tensile data; contact formulation appropriate for screw-rod interface kinematics.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening model calibrated to Ti-6Al-4V tensile coupons from same material lot (R²=0.998). Augmented Lagrangian contact with friction coefficient μ=0.23 (measured by pin-on-disc tribometry on implant-grade titanium pairs). Model form uncertainty estimated at ±3.5% for yield force QoI based on sensitivity to hardening modulus."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material and geometric inputs traceable to measurement data; input uncertainty propagated to QoI uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Screw and rod geometry inputs derived from CMM measurements of five representative components (dimensional tolerance ±0.01 mm). Material properties from certified mill test reports supplemented by in-house tensile testing. Input uncertainty propagated via Latin Hypercube Sampling (n=500) confirming QoI sensitivity dominated by rod diameter and yield strength."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N ≥ 10 constructs; samples representative of production geometry and material lot.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs tested (Lab 1: n=6, Lab 2: n=5). All constructs assembled from production-representative components from the same manufacturing lot. Dimensional inspection confirmed all within drawing tolerance. Sample size sufficient for meaningful statistical comparison per ASTM F1717 guidance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span clinically relevant range including at least two loading rates and two construct configurations.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 standard condition (quasi-static, 10 mm/min, standard vertebral body surrogate). Only one loading rate and one construct offset investigated. This factor achieves Gradation 2 rather than the required Gradation 3, representing a known gap acknowledged in the credibility assessment. Risk accepted at Medium assurance level given corroborating analytical sensitivity analyses."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model inputs matched to test-article measurements; any deviations documented and their effect on QoI bounded.",
      "rationale": "Model geometry updated to CMM measurements of each individual test construct. Material properties assigned from coupon tests on companion specimens from same lot. Torque applied to set screws matched to calibrated torque wrench values recorded during assembly. Residual input-to-model deviations bounded at <0.5% QoI impact."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10% for all primary QoIs.",
      "rationale": "E/uval values: stiffness 0.87, yield force 1.43, force at 40 mm 1.71. All below 1.96 threshold. Percent differences: 4.2%, 6.8%, 8.1% respectively, all below 10%. Acceptance criteria met for all three QoIs. Comparison performed using pooled experimental mean and combined standard uncertainty per ASME V&V 40 Section 5.3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to clinical failure mode and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs mandated by FDA guidance for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions referencing ASTM F1717. All three are directly related to the clinical failure mode of screw or rod fracture under cyclic in vivo loading. QoI relevance confirmed by clinical literature review and FDA pre-submission feedback."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
