    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All three primary QoIs meet quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is accepted at Medium assurance level given the direct co-incidence of validation scenario and COU, the corroborating analytical sensitivity results, and the Medium model risk classification. The overall credibility profile supports submission of the FEA results as supporting evidence in the 510(k) package.",
